    "They are given by (2.24)λ 3 = δ, λ 4 = δ, λ 5 = δ + ν + µs *, λ 6 = δ + ν + µ(s * -s).Eigenvalues λ 1,..., λ 5 are positive, so (A5) is reduced to the condition that λ 6 > 0 which is equivalent to(2.25) s -s * < δ + ν µ.We consider the DFE values in (2.20), (2.21).For ξ = 0 and x 1 = (0, 0, b/δ, 0, 0, 0), (2.25) reduces to b δ < δ+ν µ.",
    "Under this condition we have local asymptotic stability of x 1 when R 0 ( b δ, 0) < 1, and instability when R 0 ( b δ, 0) > 1.",
    "For ξ = 0 and x 2 = (0, 0, δ+ν µ, 0, b δ -δ+ν µ, 0), (2.25) reduces toδ + ν µ - b δ - δ + ν µ < δ + ν µ ⇐⇒ b δ > δ + ν µ.Under this condition, we have local asymptotic stability of x 2 when R 0 ( δ+ν µ, b δ -δ+ν µ) < 1, and instability when R 0 ( δ+ν µ, b δ -δ+ν µ) > 1.",
    "For ξ ∈ (0, 1] and x 3 as defined in (2.21), (2.25) reduces toδ + ν µ - b δ - δ + ν µ 2 + 4ξb µ < δ + ν µ,which holds for any positive values of the parameters, so writing x 3 = (0, 0, s 3, 0, s * 3, 0), where s 3, s * 3 are as defined in (2.21), x 3 is locally asymptotically stable when R 0 (s 3, s * 3) < 1, and unstable when R 0 (s 3, s *3) > 1.",
    "□ Remark 2.6."
